isdnMib.description: The MIB module to describe the management of ISDN interfaces.

IsdnSignalingProtocol.name: IsdnSignalingProtocol
IsdnSignalingProtocol.description: This data type is used as the syntax of the isdnSignalingProtocol object in the definition of ISDN-MIB's isdnSignalingTable. The definition of this textual convention with the addition of newly assigned values is published periodically by the IANA, in either the Assigned Numbers RFC, or some derivative of it specific to Internet Network Management number assignments. (The latest arrangements can be obtained by contacting the IANA.) Requests for new values should be made to IANA via email (iana@iana.org).

isdnBasicRateTable.name: isdnBasicRateTable
isdnBasicRateTable.description: Table containing configuration and operational parameters for all physical Basic Rate interfaces on this managed device.

isdnBasicRateEntry.name: isdnBasicRateEntry
isdnBasicRateEntry.description: An entry in the ISDN Basic Rate Table.

isdnBasicRateIfType.name: isdnBasicRateIfType
isdnBasicRateIfType.description: The physical interface type. For 'S/T' interfaces, also called 'Four-wire Basic Access Interface', the value of this object is isdns(75). For 'U' interfaces, also called 'Two-wire Basic Access Interface', the value of this object is isdnu(76).

isdnBasicRateLineTopology.name: isdnBasicRateLineTopology
isdnBasicRateLineTopology.description: The line topology to be used for this interface. Note that setting isdnBasicRateIfType to isdns(75) does not necessarily mean a line topology of point-to-multipoint.

isdnBasicRateIfMode.name: isdnBasicRateIfMode
isdnBasicRateIfMode.description: The physical interface mode. For TE mode, the value of this object is te(1). For NT mode, the value of this object is nt(2).

isdnBasicRateSignalMode.name: isdnBasicRateSignalMode
isdnBasicRateSignalMode.description: The signaling channel operational mode for this interface. If active(1) there is a signaling channel on this interface. If inactive(2) a signaling channel is not available.

isdnBearerTable.name: isdnBearerTable
isdnBearerTable.description: This table defines port specific operational, statistics and active call data for ISDN B channels. Each entry in this table describes one B (bearer) channel.

isdnBearerEntry.name: isdnBearerEntry
isdnBearerEntry.description: Operational and statistics information relating to one port. A port is a single B channel.

isdnBearerChannelType.name: isdnBearerChannelType
isdnBearerChannelType.description: The B channel type. If the B channel is connected to a dialup line, this object has a value of dialup(1). In this case, it is controlled by an associated signaling channel. If the B channel is connected to a leased line, this object has a value of leased(2). For leased line B channels, there is no signaling channel control available.

isdnBearerOperStatus.name: isdnBearerOperStatus
isdnBearerOperStatus.description: The current call control state for this port. idle(1): The B channel is idle. No call or call attempt is going on. connecting(2): A connection attempt (outgoing call) is being made on this interface. connected(3): An incoming call is in the process of validation. active(4): A call is active on this interface.

isdnBearerChannelNumber.name: isdnBearerChannelNumber
isdnBearerChannelNumber.description: The identifier being used by a signaling protocol to identify this B channel, also referred to as B channel number. If the Agent also supports the DS0 MIB, the values of isdnBearerChannelNumber and dsx0Ds0Number must be identical for a given B channel.

isdnBearerPeerAddress.name: isdnBearerPeerAddress
isdnBearerPeerAddress.description: The ISDN address the current or last call is or was connected to. In some cases, the format of this information can not be predicted, since it largely depends on the type of switch or PBX the device is connected to. Therefore, the detailed format of this information is not specified and is implementation dependent. If possible, the agent should supply this information using the E.164 format. In this case, the number must start with '+'. Otherwise, IA5 number digits must be used. If the peer ISDN address is not available, this object has a length of zero.

isdnBearerPeerSubAddress.name: isdnBearerPeerSubAddress
isdnBearerPeerSubAddress.description: The ISDN subaddress the current or last call is or was connected to. The subaddress is an user supplied string of up to 20 IA5 characters and is transmitted transparently through the network. If the peer subaddress is not available, this object has a length of zero.

isdnBearerCallOrigin.name: isdnBearerCallOrigin
isdnBearerCallOrigin.description: The call origin for the current or last call. If since system startup there was no call on this interface, this object has a value of unknown(1).

isdnBearerInfoType.name: isdnBearerInfoType
isdnBearerInfoType.reference: Q.931 [8], chapter 4.5.5, octet 3 of bearer capability information element, combined with the User Rate (as defined in octets 5 and 5a to 5d), if rate adaption is being used.
isdnBearerInfoType.description: The Information Transfer Capability for the current or last call. speech(2) refers to a non-data connection, whereas audio31(6) and audio7(7) refer to data mode connections. Note that Q.931, chapter 4.5.5, originally defined audio7(7) as '7 kHz audio' and now defines it as 'Unrestricted digital information with tones/ announcements'. If since system startup there has been no call on this interface, this object has a value of unknown(1).

isdnBearerMultirate.name: isdnBearerMultirate
isdnBearerMultirate.description: This flag indicates if the current or last call used multirate. The actual information transfer rate, in detail specified in octet 4.1 (rate multiplier), is the sum of all B channel ifSpeed values for the hyperchannel. If since system startup there was no call on this interface, this object has a value of false(2).

isdnBearerCallSetupTime.name: isdnBearerCallSetupTime
isdnBearerCallSetupTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the ISDN setup message for the current or last call was sent or received. If since system startup there has been no call on this interface, this object has a value of zero.

isdnBearerCallConnectTime.name: isdnBearerCallConnectTime
isdnBearerCallConnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the ISDN connect message for the current or last call was sent or received. If since system startup there has been no call on this interface, this object has a value of zero.

isdnBearerChargedUnits.name: isdnBearerChargedUnits
isdnBearerChargedUnits.description: The number of charged units for the current or last connection. For incoming calls or if charging information is not supplied by the switch, the value of this object is zero.

isdnSignalingGetIndex.name: isdnSignalingGetIndex
isdnSignalingGetIndex.description: The recommended procedure for selecting a new index for isdnSignalingTable row creation is to GET the value of this object, and then to SET the object with the same value. If the SET operation succeeds, the manager can use this value as an index to create a new row in this table.

isdnSignalingTable.name: isdnSignalingTable
isdnSignalingTable.description: ISDN signaling table containing configuration and operational parameters for all ISDN signaling channels on this managed device.

isdnSignalingEntry.name: isdnSignalingEntry
isdnSignalingEntry.description: An entry in the ISDN Signaling Table. To create a new entry, only isdnSignalingProtocol needs to be specified before isdnSignalingStatus can become active(1).

isdnSignalingIndex.name: isdnSignalingIndex
isdnSignalingIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies an entry in the isdnSignalingTable.

isdnSignalingIfIndex.name: isdnSignalingIfIndex
isdnSignalingIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface associated with this signaling channel.

isdnSignalingProtocol.name: isdnSignalingProtocol
isdnSignalingProtocol.description: The particular protocol type supported by the switch providing access to the ISDN network to which this signaling channel is connected.

isdnSignalingCallingAddress.name: isdnSignalingCallingAddress
isdnSignalingCallingAddress.description: The ISDN Address to be assigned to this signaling channel. More specifically, this is the 'Calling Address information element' as being passed to the switch in outgoing call setup messages. It can be an EAZ (1TR6), a calling number (DSS1, ETSI) or any other number necessary to identify a signaling interface. If there is no such number defined or required, this is a zero length string. It is represented in DisplayString form. Incoming calls can also be identified by this number. If the Directory Number, i.e. the Called Number in incoming calls, is different to this number, the isdnDirectoryTable has to be used to specify all possible Directory Numbers. The format of this information largely depends on the type of switch or PBX the device is connected to. Therefore, the detailed format of this information is not specified and is implementation dependent. If possible, the agent should implement this information using the E.164 number format. In this case, the number must start with '+'. Otherwise, IA5 number digits must be used.

isdnSignalingSubAddress.name: isdnSignalingSubAddress
isdnSignalingSubAddress.description: Supplementary information to the ISDN address assigned to this signaling channel. Usually, this is the subaddress as defined in Q.931. If there is no such number defined or required, this is a zero length string. The subaddress is used for incoming calls as well as for outgoing calls. The subaddress is an user supplied string of up to 20 IA5 characters and is transmitted transparently through the network.

isdnSignalingBchannelCount.name: isdnSignalingBchannelCount
isdnSignalingBchannelCount.description: The total number of B channels (bearer channels) managed by this signaling channel. The default value of this object depends on the physical interface type and is either 2 for Basic Rate interfaces or 24 (30) for Primary Rate interfaces.

isdnSignalingInfoTrapEnable.name: isdnSignalingInfoTrapEnable
isdnSignalingInfoTrapEnable.description: Indicates whether isdnMibCallInformation traps should be generated for calls on this signaling channel.

isdnSignalingStatus.name: isdnSignalingStatus
isdnSignalingStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the isdnSignalingTable.

isdnSignalingStatsTable.name: isdnSignalingStatsTable
isdnSignalingStatsTable.description: ISDN signaling table containing statistics information for all ISDN signaling channels on this managed device. Only statistical information which is not already being counted in the ifTable is being defined in this table.

isdnSignalingStatsEntry.name: isdnSignalingStatsEntry
isdnSignalingStatsEntry.description: An entry in the ISDN Signaling statistics Table.

isdnSigStatsInCalls.name: isdnSigStatsInCalls
isdnSigStatsInCalls.description: The number of incoming calls on this interface.

isdnSigStatsInConnected.name: isdnSigStatsInConnected
isdnSigStatsInConnected.description: The number of incoming calls on this interface which were actually connected.

isdnSigStatsOutCalls.name: isdnSigStatsOutCalls
isdnSigStatsOutCalls.description: The number of outgoing calls on this interface.

isdnSigStatsOutConnected.name: isdnSigStatsOutConnected
isdnSigStatsOutConnected.description: The number of outgoing calls on this interface which were actually connected.

isdnSigStatsChargedUnits.name: isdnSigStatsChargedUnits
isdnSigStatsChargedUnits.description: The number of charging units on this interface since system startup. Only the charging units applying to the local interface, i.e. for originated calls or for calls with 'Reverse charging' being active, are counted here.

isdnLapdTable.name: isdnLapdTable
isdnLapdTable.description: Table containing configuration and statistics information for all LAPD (D channel Data Link) interfaces on this managed device. Only statistical information which is not already being counted in the ifTable is being defined in this table.

isdnLapdEntry.name: isdnLapdEntry
isdnLapdEntry.description: An entry in the LAPD Table.

isdnLapdPrimaryChannel.name: isdnLapdPrimaryChannel
isdnLapdPrimaryChannel.reference: Q.931 [8], Annex F, D channel backup procedures.
isdnLapdPrimaryChannel.description: If set to true(1), this D channel is the designated primary D channel if D channel backup is active. There must be exactly one primary D channel configured. If D channel backup is not used, this object has a value of true(1).

isdnLapdOperStatus.name: isdnLapdOperStatus
isdnLapdOperStatus.description: The operational status of this interface: inactive all layers are inactive l1Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink not established l2Active layer 1 is activated, layer 2 datalink established.

isdnLapdPeerSabme.name: isdnLapdPeerSabme
isdnLapdPeerSabme.description: The number of peer SABME frames received on this interface. This is the number of peer-initiated new connections on this interface.

isdnLapdRecvdFrmr.name: isdnLapdRecvdFrmr
isdnLapdRecvdFrmr.description: The number of LAPD FRMR response frames received. This is the number of framing errors on this interface.

isdnEndpointGetIndex.name: isdnEndpointGetIndex
isdnEndpointGetIndex.description: The recommended procedure for selecting a new index for isdnEndpointTable row creation is to GET the value of this object, and then to SET the object with the same value. If the SET operation succeeds, the manager can use this value as an index to create a new row in this table.

isdnEndpointTable.name: isdnEndpointTable
isdnEndpointTable.description: Table containing configuration for Terminal Endpoints.

isdnEndpointEntry.name: isdnEndpointEntry
isdnEndpointEntry.description: An entry in the Terminal Endpoint Table. The value of isdnEndpointIfType must be supplied for a row in this table to become active.

isdnEndpointIndex.name: isdnEndpointIndex
isdnEndpointIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies an entry in the isdnEndpointTable.

isdnEndpointIfIndex.name: isdnEndpointIfIndex
isdnEndpointIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface associated with this Terminal Endpoint.

isdnEndpointIfType.name: isdnEndpointIfType
isdnEndpointIfType.description: The interface type for this Terminal Endpoint. Interface types of x25ple(40) and isdn(63) are allowed. The interface type is identical to the value of ifType in the associated ifEntry.

isdnEndpointTeiType.name: isdnEndpointTeiType
isdnEndpointTeiType.description: The type of TEI (Terminal Endpoint Identifier) used for this Terminal Endpoint. In case of dynamic(1), the TEI value is selected by the switch. In case of static(2), a valid TEI value has to be entered in the isdnEndpointTeiValue object. The default value for this object depends on the interface type as well as the Terminal Endpoint type. On Primary Rate interfaces the default value is static(2). On Basic Rate interfaces the default value is dynamic(1) for isdn(63) Terminal Endpoints and static(2) for x25ple(40) Terminal Endpoints.

isdnEndpointTeiValue.name: isdnEndpointTeiValue
isdnEndpointTeiValue.description: The TEI (Terminal Endpoint Identifier) value for this Terminal Endpoint. If isdnEndpointTeiType is set to static(2), valid numbers are 0..63, while otherwise the value is set internally. The default value of this object is 0 for static TEI assignment. The default value for dynamic TEI assignment is also 0 as long as no TEI has been assigned. After TEI assignment, the assigned TEI value is returned.

isdnEndpointSpid.name: isdnEndpointSpid
isdnEndpointSpid.reference: Bellcore SR-NWT-001953, Generic Guidelines for ISDN Terminal Equipment on Basic Access Interfaces, Chapter 8.5.1.
isdnEndpointSpid.description: The Service profile IDentifier (SPID) information for this Terminal Endpoint. The SPID is composed of 9-20 numeric characters. This information has to be defined in addition to the local number for some switch protocol types, e.g. Bellcore NI-1 and NI-2. If this object is not required, it is a zero length string.

isdnEndpointStatus.name: isdnEndpointStatus
isdnEndpointStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the isdnEndpointTable.

isdnDirectoryEntry.name: isdnDirectoryEntry
isdnDirectoryEntry.description: An entry in the Directory Number Table. All objects in an entry must be set for a new row to become active.

isdnDirectoryIndex.name: isdnDirectoryIndex
isdnDirectoryIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies an entry in the isdnDirectoryTable.

isdnDirectoryNumber.name: isdnDirectoryNumber
isdnDirectoryNumber.description: A Directory Number. Directory Numbers are used to identify incoming calls on the signaling channel given in isdnDirectorySigIndex. The format of this information largely depends on the type of switch or PBX the device is connected to. Therefore, the detailed format of this information is not specified and is implementation dependent. If possible, the agent should implement this information using the E.164 number format. In this case, the number must start with '+'. Otherwise, IA5 number digits must be used.

isdnDirectorySigIndex.name: isdnDirectorySigIndex
isdnDirectorySigIndex.description: An index pointing to an ISDN signaling channel. Incoming calls are accepted on this signaling channel if the isdnDirectoryNumber is presented as Called Number in the SETUP message.

isdnDirectoryStatus.name: isdnDirectoryStatus
isdnDirectoryStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete rows in the isdnDirectoryTable.

isdnMibCallInformation.name: isdnMibCallInformation
isdnMibCallInformation.description: This trap/inform is sent to the manager under the following condidions: - on incoming calls for each call which is rejected for policy reasons (e.g. unknown neighbor or access violation) - on outgoing calls whenever a call attempt is determined to have ultimately failed. In the event that call retry is active, then this will be after all retry attempts have failed. - whenever a call connects. In this case, the object isdnBearerCallConnectTime should be included in the trap. Only one such trap is sent in between successful or unsuccessful call attempts from or to a single neighbor; subsequent call attempts result in no trap. If the Dial Control MIB objects dialCtlNbrCfgId and dialCtlNbrCfgIndex are known by the entity generating this trap, both objects should be included in the trap as well. The receipt of this trap with no dial neighbor information indicates that the manager must poll the callHistoryTable of the Dial Control MIB to see what changed.

isdnMibCompliance.name: isdnMibCompliance
isdnMibCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the ISDN MIB.

isdnMibBasicRateGroup.name: isdnMibBasicRateGroup
isdnMibBasicRateGroup.description: A collection of objects required for ISDN Basic Rate physical interface configuration and statistics.

isdnMibBearerGroup.name: isdnMibBearerGroup
isdnMibBearerGroup.description: A collection of objects required for ISDN Bearer channel control and statistics.

isdnMibSignalingGroup.name: isdnMibSignalingGroup
isdnMibSignalingGroup.description: A collection of objects required for ISDN D channel configuration and statistics.

isdnMibEndpointGroup.name: isdnMibEndpointGroup
isdnMibEndpointGroup.description: A collection of objects describing Terminal Endpoints.

isdnMibDirectoryGroup.name: isdnMibDirectoryGroup
isdnMibDirectoryGroup.description: A collection of objects describing directory numbers.
